<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css"/>  
  <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
  <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/fdf00391bb.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <title>About</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="main-content">
    {{>header}}

    <section class="about">
      <h2 class="about__title">About This App</h2>
      
      <p class="about__body">
        This weather application was created by <strong>Renee Messersmith</strong>
        as a project to practice building web applications with Node.js and working with
        third-party APIs.
      </p>

      <p class="about__body">
        The app allows users to search for locations and view current weather
        conditions using real-time data. It focuses on simplicity, accessibility,
        and clear presentation of information.
      </p>

      <p class="about__body">
        Weather data is provided by 
        <a href="https://weatherstack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Weatherstack</a>, and location data is provided by 
        <a href="https://positionstack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Positionstack</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="about__body">
        This project was built using modern web technologies such as HTML, 
        CSS, JavaScript, Node.js, and server-side rendering with Handlebars.
      </p>

      <img
        class="portrait"
        src="./img/Renee Messersmith.jpg"
        alt="Portrait of Renee Messersmith"
      />
    </section>
  </div>

  {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>